Mad Scientist: Alchemy 150</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udarial1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darial1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/15/01 11:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm34.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.truepath.com/jadae/Darial.JPG width=120 height=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who's leaving, Who's staying, Who's playing both?</span><hr size=1> Some things I really like:<br>
<br>
Quest rewards are appropriate for your class!<br>
A druid, a mentalist, and my Blademistress all did the same quest and received different items that enhanced stats important to our respective classes.  That imho, rocks!<br>
<br>
The graphics are very detailed - much more so than EQ.<br>
<br>
The grouping tool where you can 'find' people who are lfg anywhere within your realm is a nice feature.<br>
<br>
Minimal downtime!  Sit and rest for 1-2 minutes and my health is ready to go!  Not nearly as much sitting around as in EQ.<br>
<br>
Trade skills are less likely to give you carpal tunnel to become a master! I really like how thought out this is.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some things not too sure about yet:<br>
<br>
I /appealed for a quest that wasn't working and hadn't received a response after 2 days.  I'm sure they were busy it being the first weekend so we'll see.<br>
<br>
Jadae's propensity for killing you just so he can rez you...<br>
<br>
I still haven't found a good spot for the chat window where it doesn't interfere with my view.  Also making the window see thru also effects the text so while you can see you can't see what was said.  *this one's picky I know*<br>
<br>
I have the minimum req of a pII 450, 256m RAM, 32m video and have found spots where my system just couldn't handle the polygons.  even with driver updates.  *Just bought a new mb and cpu after this weekend*<br>
<br>
Overall I think there are many very very good things about this game that EQ is going to have a hard time beating.  I don't think I'll be quitting EQ, but I am going to divide my time at the least.<br>
<br>
Darial <br>
Sol Invictus <br>
