<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Since the classes are so unbalanaced this doesnt sound very appealing either.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
No idea what you're talking about here.  They seem extremely balanced to me.  If you mean that a Ranger will own you in three steps.. well, don't charge a guy who is a master of the Bow when he has an arrow loaded and 19 more on his shoulder. *shrug*  I just don't see what the hell you're talkign about.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;This game has very little content and what content it HAS is taken directly from EQ.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, you must be dreaming or dropping acid.  I have done MORE interesting stuff in my newbie time in DAoC than I ever dreamed of in EQ.  Get this...  Lower levels ARE FUN!  EQ SUCKED ASS for the lower levels.  In DAoC at lvl 11 I feel like a veteran.  I have kicked all sorts of ass, saved a town, rescued about 4 damsels in distress, helped a Lurikeen who cussed me out, seen a haunted tomb and honestly got a cold chill, watched Olav die, infiltrated my own people, participated in the spy circuit, been to the outskirts of the Unselee Court, and managed to take on some xp mobs all alone.  And at NO POINT DURING THIS DID I FRET OVER XP LOSS OR LOSING MY CORPSE.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Oh great, a kidney punch combo. That is little more then window dressing as far as I'm concerned...&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, what game are you talking about!?  I don't know of any kidney punch combos.  If you are referring to combat styles, I assure you they are FAR MORE than window dressing.  There are High-Med fatigue anytime styles and then there are situational styles, which leads to chained styles.  The fight can hinge on the proper execution of this which is TOTALLY MANUAL.  EQ never even dreamed of this.  I can cause a DoT type effect called a &quot;bleed&quot; if I execute a spear move after I Evade a creature's attack.  If I can pull off a Hunter's Boon, I can hamstring the mob, causing it to move slower.  I use Hunter's Barb to taunt OFF of me and Forest Spear to taunt ON to me.<br>
<br>
Then I switch to my Spiked Club and Shield.  With my spiked club I can aim to stun, aim to crack ribs, or get behind them for a smash.  With my shield I can set to guard the Healer, I can bash with it and block with it.  EQ, my ass!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;I just cant see an EQ clone pulilng me away from EQ, when the original can give me the same thing.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I wouldn't enjoy an EQ clone much either.  You should try Dark Age of Camelot.  It's this new game.. it's great.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;The servers are sure stable though, woo hoo!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
And your EQ servers should be very stable as well, running at below half capacity.<br>
